<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Newswall</title>
    <style>
        li {margin: 5px;}
        .emulator {
            height: 2560px;
            width: 1440px;
            filter: grayscale(100);
            border: 50px solid black;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Newswall</h1>
<p>This is a little node.js website to render newspapers for
    <a href="https://www.visionect.com/shop/place-play-32/ref/pathikrit/" target="_blank">e-ink displays</a>
    (original idea by <a href="https://onezero.medium.com/the-morning-paper-revisited-35b407822494" target="_blank">Max Braun</a>):</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <a href="/latest"><code>/latest</code></a>: Cycles through front pages of newspapers on each refresh.
        <i>You should point your e-ink device to this.</i>
        <br/>This server is <a href="https://github.com/pathikrit/newswall/blob/master/app.js#L15" target="_blank">configured</a> to support the following:
        <ol>
            <% papers.forEach((paper) => { %>
                <li><%=paper.name%>: <a href="/latest?papers=<%=paper.id%>"><code>/latest?papers=<%=paper.id%></code></a></li>
            <% }) %>
        </ol>
        <% if (papers.length > 1) { %>
            e.g. to display only <%= papers[0].name %> or <%= papers[1].name %> (when available):
            <a href="/latest?papers=<%= papers.slice(0, 2).map(p => p.id).join(',') %>"><code>/latest?papers=<%= papers.slice(0, 2).map(p => p.id).join(',') %></code></a>
        <% } %>
    </li>
    <li><a href="/archive"><code>/archive</code></a>: Browse the raw newspaper files on the server. Most of the papers come from <a href="https://www.freedomforum.org/todaysfrontpages/" target="_blank">The Freedom Forum</a> - please consider <a href="https://www.freedomforum.org/support/" target="_blank">supporting</a> them.
</ul>
<p>Checkout the <a href="https://github.com/pathikrit/newswall" target="_blank">project on Github</a> for more details.</p>
<div style="text-align: center">
    <h2>Emulator</h2>
    <iframe class="emulator" src="/latest"></iframe>
</div>
</body>
</html>
